<p>I have a div/image: <code>.drop</code> and I want some text to appear: <code>.text_drop</code> when hovering over it. <code>.drop</code> is an image and so is <code>.text_drop</code>, but <code>.drop:hover</code> also has an animation to it. Anyways, <code>.text_drop</code> doesn't appear, when hovering over <code>.drop</code>.</p>  <p>Codes looks like this:</p>  <pre><code>.drop {     position: absolute;     z-index: 3;     width: 15vw;     height: auto;     top: 75vw;     left: 0vw; } .text_drop {     position: absolute;     z-index: 3;     width: 15vw;     height: auto;     top:90vw;     left: 0vw; }  .drop:hover {     -webkit-animation-name: puls;     -webkit-animation-duration: 0.5s;     -webkit-animation-iteration-count:infinite;     -webkit-animation-direction:alternate-reverse; }  @-webkit-keyframes puls {     from{         transform: scale(0.9);     }     to{         transform: scale(1);     }     } </code></pre>